						               													<description>The first cooperative game for toddlers. The three little pigs have to go home before the wolf.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Three little pigs is a simple game from 2 years old and which takes around 10 minutes to play. It is ideal to start learning the rules.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The board represent three paths to pig's house plus another for the wolf. Players roll a dice each turn which have a different color in each side.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Yellow, red and blue allow one of the pigs to move to the next square if it match the color. White allows the player to move a pig of his choice. Black implies to move the wolf closer to the house and the flower allows the player to take one of the flower tiles that could lead to the three pigs moving one square each closer to the house or a movement for the wolf.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The players win if the three pigs reach the house before the wolf does. They lose if the wolf arrives before.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
